2025-01-07 12:46 ET - News Release
Mr. Louis-Pierre Gignac  
 reports
G MINING VENTURES RECEIVES INTERIM ENVIRONMENTAL PERMIT FOR THE OKO WEST GOLD PROJECT IN GUYANA
G Mining Ventures Corp. has received an interim environmental permit (IEP) from Guyana's Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) in response to its environmental impact assessment (EIA) and environmental impact statement (EIS) submissions (jointly, environmental and social impact assessment (ESIA)) made in November, 2024, for the corporation's Oko West gold project.
The IEP is valid for one year and, together with the no-objection letter received from the Guyana Forestry Commission, G Mining has fulfilled the requirements to initiate early works construction activities.
G Mining intends to advance the following early works activities in the first half of 2025:
Barge landing facility;
Main access road and internal roads;
Airstrip;
Permanent camp facility;
Water and sewage treatment plants;
Power generation and communication tower.
"The approval of the interim environmental permit represents an important step in reaching a construction decision for the Oko West project," commented Louis-Pierre Gignac, president and chief executive officer. "The receipt of this permit supports a collaborative engagement between Guyana's EPA, Forestry Commission and nearby communities in Region 7 ensuring alignment with GMIN's mine development activities in-country.
   We are excited to have the opportunity to commence early works activities ahead of schedule and to grow the local team in preparation for the main construction phase."
The public can access the Oko EIA and EIS submissions in the National Library, University Library, the Regional Democratic Council Region 7 office and on G Mining's website (Oko West gold project page).
Following a 60-day comment period, EPA review of the submission, disclosure meetings and publication of the final ESIA report, the EPA will reach a decision with respect to the granting of the final environmental permit for Oko West.
Looking ahead, additional development catalysts at Oko West include:
Commencement of early works (Q1 2025);
Feasibility study publication (Q2 2025);
Full permit (Q2 2025);
Formal construction decision (second half of 2025);
Continuation of detailed engineering (2025).
Greenfield and brownfield exploration (2025)
